{{朝鲜政治}}
'''朝鲜民主主义人民共和国互联网'''的使用情况与其他国家有所不同。在[[朝鲜民主主义人民共和国|朝鲜]]，人们只有经过特别许可才能访问[[互联网|互联网]]。朝鲜的互联网主要由政府部门和在朝外国人使用。朝鲜拥有一系列[[宽频|宽频]]基础设施，例如各机构之间的[[光纤|光纤]]网络。<ref>[https://sites.google.com/site/internethistoryasia/country-region-information/north-korea-korea-democratic-peoples-republic-of North Korea (Korea, Democratic People's Republic of) – Asia Internet History Projects] {{Wayback|url=https://sites.google.com/site/internethistoryasia/country-region-information/north-korea-korea-democratic-peoples-republic-of |date=20210326141923 }}. Sites.google.com (2012-09-26). Retrieved on 2013-03-20.</ref>但是在大多数情况下，个人和机构所使用的网络是国内唯一的免费[[内联网|内联网]]，这个网络被称为“[[光明网_(朝鲜)|光明网]]”。只有极少数人拥有国际互联网的访问权限。<ref>[http://www.computerworld.com/s/article/9177968/North_Korea_moves_quietly_onto_the_Internet?taxonomyId=18&pageNumber=2 North Korea moves quietly onto the Internet] {{Wayback|url=http://www.computerworld.com/s/article/9177968/North_Korea_moves_quietly_onto_the_Internet?taxonomyId=18&pageNumber=2 |date=20140226231627 }}. Computerworld (2010-06-10). Retrieved on 2013-03-20.</ref>

2006年，[[无国界记者|无国界记者]]组织称朝鲜是“迄今为止互联网上最严重的黑洞”。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2006/10/23/technology/23link.html?_r=0|date=2006-10-23|title=The Internet Black Hole That Is North Korea|publisher=The New York Times|accessdate=2016-09-05|archive-date=2020-11-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201127012758/http://www.nytimes.com/2006/10/23/technology/23link.html?_r=0|dead-url=no}}</ref>在[[保护记者委员会|保护记者委员会]]于2015年发布的“[[互联网审查|互联网审查]]最严格的十个国家”榜单中，朝鲜位居第二{{NoteTag|在[[亚洲|亚洲]]则是第一}}，仅次于[[厄立特里亚|厄立特里亚]]。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cpj.org/2015/04/10-most-censored-countries.php|title=10 Most Censored Countries|publisher=Committee to Protect Journalists|access-date=2016-09-05|archive-date=2016-06-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160611062550/https://cpj.org/2015/04/10-most-censored-countries.php|dead-url=no}}</ref>2020年，网站视觉资本（VisualCapitalist）与Datareportal数码平台的报告显示，朝鲜互联网使用率为0%，为全球唯一沒有成规模网民的国家<ref>{{Cite web|title=报告：朝鲜互联网使用率为0% 全球唯一禁居民上网国家 {{!}} 国际|url=https://www.orientaldaily.com.my/news/international/2020/08/23/359262|accessdate=2020-08-23|work=東方網 馬來西亞東方日報|language=zh-Hans}}</ref>。

== 概况 ==
朝鲜的互联网由国内独家[[互联网服务供应商|互联网服务供应商]]——[[星合营会社|星合营会社]]（Star Joint Venture Co.）提供，它是[[朝鲜递信贸易会社|朝鲜递信贸易会社]]与[[泰国|泰国]][[洛士利太平洋|洛士利太平洋]]（Loxley Pacific）合资的企业。从2009年12月21日开始，朝鲜互联网的[[IP地址|IP地址]]分配由该公司控制<ref>IP地址段175.45.176.0/22的[[WHOIS|WHOIS]]查询结果</ref>。在成立星合营会社之前，朝鲜只能通过与德国相连的[[卫星网络|卫星网络]]，或者在政府需要时直连到[[中国联通|中国联通]]或[[TransTeleCom|俄罗斯TransTeleCom电信公司]]的线路来访问互联网<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bgp.he.net/AS131279|title=AS131279 Ryugyong-dong|accessdate=2017-10-08|author=[[Hurricane_Electric|Hurricane Electric]]|publisher=Hurricane Electric|language=en|archive-date=2015-09-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150906075240/http://bgp.he.net/AS131279|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.zaobao.com.sg/realtime/world/story20171003-800166|title=俄罗斯电信商为朝鲜互联网开新路|date=2017-10-03|accessdate=2017-10-08|author=陈慧璋|publisher=[[联合早报|联合早报]]|language=zh-sg|archive-date=2019-06-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190629112217/https://www.zaobao.com.sg/realtime/world/story20171003-800166|dead-url=no}}</ref>。现在朝鲜几乎所有的互联网流量都会通过中国路由<ref name="CNN2014">Pagliery, Jose (December 22, 2014). [http://money.cnn.com/2014/12/22/technology/security/north-korean-internet/index.html "A peek into North Korea's Internet".] {{Wayback|url=http://money.cnn.com/2014/12/22/technology/security/north-korean-internet/index.html |date=20201202133756 }} ''CNN''. Retrieved December 23, 2014.</ref>。

从2013年2月开始，位于朝鲜的外国人可以通过[[高丽电信|高丽电信]]提供的[[3G|3G]]服务进行手机上网<ref name=bbc-20130222>{{cite news |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/technology-21546877 |title=North Korea to offer mobile internet access |publisher=BBC |date=22 February 2013 |accessdate=15 July 2014 |archive-date=2014-10-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141017054038/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/technology-21546877 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=wp-20130226>{{cite news |url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/worldviews/wp/2013/02/26/instagrams-from-within-north-korea-lift-the-veil-but-only-slightly/ |title=Instagrams from within North Korea lift the veil, but only slightly |author=Caitlin Dewey |newspaper=Washington Post |date=26 February 2013 |accessdate=15 July 2014 |archive-date=2014-07-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140719150136/http://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/worldviews/wp/2013/02/26/instagrams-from-within-north-korea-lift-the-veil-but-only-slightly/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=guardian-20150623>{{cite news |url=http://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/jun/23/north-korea-blocks-photosharing-app |title=North Korea blocks access to Instagram |newspaper=The Guardian |agency=Associated Press |date=23 June 2015 |accessdate=23 June 2015 |archive-date=2020-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201206030103/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/jun/23/north-korea-blocks-photosharing-app |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

在朝鲜，互联网的访问权限受到了极其严厉的限制。2016年，研究机构“We are social”发布调查报告，表示朝鲜只有7,200名互联网使用者，占全国人口数量的0.03%<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thenextweb.com/asia/2016/01/28/there-are-just-7000-web-users-in-north-korea/|title=There are just 7,000 Web users in North Korea|publisher=The Next Web|date=2016-01-28|access-date=2016-09-05|archive-date=2021-02-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210226070627/https://thenextweb.com/asia/2016/01/28/there-are-just-7000-web-users-in-north-korea/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，可以不受限制访问互联网的人往往自称是高官、[[非政府组织|非政府组织]]成员或外国大使<ref name=CNN2014/><ref name=Diplomat>Tae-jun Kang (August 14, 2014). [http://thediplomat.com/2014/08/wi-fi-access-sparks-housing-boom-in-pyongyang/ "Wi-Fi Access Sparks Housing Boom in Pyongyang."] {{Wayback|url=http://thediplomat.com/2014/08/wi-fi-access-sparks-housing-boom-in-pyongyang/ |date=20201115041039 }} ''[[The_Diplomat|The Diplomat]]''</ref>。朝鲜领袖[[金正日|金正日]]也表示自己热爱“网上冲浪”。<ref name=lankov244/>按照{{le|Incapsula|Incapsula}}安全研究员奥弗·嘎耶的说法，朝鲜全国的网络流量痕迹比[[福克兰群岛|福克兰群岛]]还要少<ref name=Sydney2014/><ref name="nyti_Corr">{{Cite web| title = Correction: NKorea-Mystery Outage Story| author1 = The Associated Press| author2 = Raphael Satter| work = [[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]| date = 24 December 2014| accessdate = 28 February 2015| url = http://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2014/12/24/world/europe/ap-eu-nkorea-mystery-outage.html| archive-date = 2015-04-03| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150403144239/http://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2014/12/24/world/europe/ap-eu-nkorea-mystery-outage.html| dead-url = no}}</ref>。同时身为《[[东亚日报|东亚日报]]》记者和[[脱北者|脱北者]]的[[朱成夏|朱成夏]]指出，截止到2014年，朝鲜政府已经用光明网来限制[[全球網際網路使用率|互联网使用率]]，特别是在旅馆等环境。尽管大多数大学校园已经能够访问光明网，政府还是会“严格监控网络访问”<ref name=Diplomat/>。对于互联网的存在，朝鲜很多国民可能浑然不知<ref name="CNN2014"/>。

但是，朝鲜的信息技术产业正在增长，对互联网访问的需求量也在增加<ref>{{cite news | first = Jean H. | last = Lee | title = North Korea's 'Digital Revolution' Under Way | date = 2011-07-25 | url = http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2011/07/25/digital-revolution-north-korea_n_908368.html | agency = Associated Press | accessdate = 2011-08-08 | archive-date = 2012-03-03 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120303132857/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2011/07/25/digital-revolution-north-korea_n_908368.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>。在2010年10月，[[朝鲜中央通讯社|朝-{}-鲜中央通讯社]]网站通过朝鲜的服务器和朝鲜IP地址上线，这是已知的第一个直接连往互联网的朝鲜网站<ref>[http://www.northkoreatech.org/2010/10/09/the-new-face-of-kcna/ The new face of KCNA « North Korea Tech] {{Wayback|url=http://www.northkoreatech.org/2010/10/09/the-new-face-of-kcna/ |date=20210131163746 }}. Northkoreatech.org (2010-10-09). Retrieved on 2013-03-20.</ref>。与此同时，10月9日，参加[[朝鲜劳动党|朝-{}-鲜劳动党]]成立65周年庆典的外国记者可以在专门安排的记者室内完整地访问互联网<ref>[http://www.computerworld.com/s/article/9190238/North_Korea_opens_up_Internet_for_national_anniversary North Korea opens up Internet for national anniversary] {{Wayback|url=http://www.computerworld.com/s/article/9190238/North_Korea_opens_up_Internet_for_national_anniversary |date=20140709001749 }}. Computerworld (2010-10-09). Retrieved on 2013-03-20.</ref><ref>{{cite news | first = Min-jeong (민정) | last = Cho (조) | title = 北 웹사이트 접속 늘어…윈도XP 사용 | date = 2011-04-30 | url = http://www.yonhapnews.co.kr/bulletin/2011/04/30/0200000000AKR20110430025600014.HTML | work = Yonhap News | accessdate = 2011-12-08 | language = ko | archive-date = 2017-10-08 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20171008230902/http://www.yonhapnews.co.kr/bulletin/2011/04/30/0200000000AKR20110430025600014.HTML | dead-url = no }}</ref>。不过，由于朝鲜政府的孤立政策，人们很难了解朝鲜电子产业的发展情况。[[苹果公司|苹果]]、[[索尼|索尼]]和[[微软|微软]]公司禁止将其产品销往朝鲜，所以有第三方公司购买他们的产品，并将其作为自己的商品销售给朝鲜客户<ref name=CNN2014/>。

从2016年4月开始，朝鲜封锁了[[Facebook|Facebook]]、[[YouTube|YouTube]]、[[Twitter|Twitter]]和[[大韩民国|大韩民国]]的网站，因为“对网上信息的传播表示关切”<ref>{{Cite web| title = North Korea blocks Facebook, Twitter and YouTuber| work = [[The_Associated_Press|The Associated Press]]| date = 4 April 2016| accessdate = 4 April 2016| url = http://globalnews.ca/news/2616449/north-korea-blacks-facebook-twitter-and-youtube/| archive-date = 2016-04-06| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160406095746/http://globalnews.ca/news/2616449/north-korea-blacks-facebook-twitter-and-youtube/| dead-url = no}}</ref>。

== 朝鲜政府对互联网的使用 ==

=== 网站 ===
在2005年，朝鲜政府运营的网站数量在30个左右。<ref>{{cite news|work=PhysOrg.com|title=North Korea's baby steps for the Internet|date=2005-08-30|url=http://www.physorg.com/news6109.html|publisher=United Press International|accessdate=2016-09-05|archive-date=2012-03-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120315124744/http://www.physorg.com/news6109.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>2004年，韩国警方识别出了43家运行在外国服务器上的亲朝网站。警方在报告中称，这些网站鼓励对韩国和西方国家的敌视态度，并积极正面描绘朝鲜。 根据《[[东亚日报|东亚日报]]》报道，在韩国之外运营的亲朝网站包括位于日本的“Joseon Tongsin”和“Guk-jeonseon”、位于中国的“Unification Arirang”、位于美国的“Minjok Tongsin”，此外还有12个新上线的亲朝网站，例如“Korea Network”。<ref>{{cite news|periodical=[[The_Dong-a_Ilbo|The Dong-a Ilbo]]|url=http://english.donga.com/srv/service.php3?biid=2004090935168|date=2004-09-08|last=Yoon|first=Jong-Koo|title=Police Announce 43 Active Pro-North Korean Websites|accessdate=2016-09-05|archive-date=2015-02-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150226140909/http://english.donga.com/srv/service.php3?biid=2004090935168|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2010年8月，[[BBC|BBC]]新闻报道指出由朝鲜政府签约的网络代理服务商已为“[[我们民族之间|我们民族之间]]”开设了官方YouTube频道、Facebook主页和Twitter账户。Twitter和YouTube账户都使用[[朝鲜语|-{zh:朝鮮語; zh-cn:朝鲜语; zh-tw:韓語; zh-hk:韓語; zh-sg:韩语;}-]]。BBC还指出，“朝鲜方面在最近的Twitter推文中指出韩国当前的行政部门是美国人的‘妓女’。”<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-11007825 | work=BBC News | title=North Korea creates Twitter and YouTube presence | date=2010-08-18 | accessdate=2016-09-05 | archive-date=2021-03-08 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308133632/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-11007825 | dead-url=no }}</ref>

此外，朝鲜各网站都会包含一个突出显示领导人姓名的特殊程序。<ref name="bbc_2012">{{cite news|url=http://www.bbc.com/zhongwen/simp/world/2012/12/121210_world_north_korea_internet.shtml|publisher=BBC中文网|author=戴夫·李|date=2012-12-10|title=朝鲜：最隐秘国家的互联网|accessdate=2016-09-05|archive-date=2019-06-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190629111323/https://www.bbc.com/zhongwen/simp/world/2012/12/121210_world_north_korea_internet.shtml|dead-url=no}}</ref>按照规定，朝鲜已故最高领导人[[金日成|金日成]]、[[金正日|金正日]]和现任最高领导人[[金正恩|金正恩]]的名字出现在[[光明网_(朝鲜)|光明网]]内的任何一个网站上时，他们的姓名字体必须比页面上的标准字体大10%~20%。<ref name="hackread">{{cite web|url=http://www.hackread.com/how-bad-is-the-north-korean-cyber-threat/|title=How Bad is the North Korean Cyber Threat?|date=2016-01-20|publisher=Hackread|access-date=2016-09-05|archive-date=2021-01-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210120084054/https://www.hackread.com/how-bad-is-the-north-korean-cyber-threat/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

在2016年9月21日上午约5点钟（[[协调世界时|UTC]]）时，朝鲜的一台[[.kp|.kp]]域名服务器ns2.kptc.kp被误配置允许全球[[DNS|DNS]]区域转移。而部分有关朝鲜互联网的记述细节因此次操作失误被泄露。泄露的结果显示朝鲜掌控的.kp域名下只有28个可访问的网站。目前该问题已经被朝鲜当局修复。<ref>{{cite web|author1=mandatoryprogrammer|title=North Korea .kp TLD Zone Data|url=https://github.com/mandatoryprogrammer/NorthKoreaDNSLeak|website=Github|publisher=Github|accessdate=2016-09-24|archive-date=2016-09-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160921171448/https://github.com/mandatoryprogrammer/NorthKoreaDNSLeak|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 黑客活动 ===
[[朝鮮人民軍第121局|朝鲜121局]]是朝鲜目前拥有的一支网络部队，编制大约1800人，成员全部是训练有素的精英。目前第一次已知的网络的攻击大约发生在2000年。2013年，朝鲜针对韩国媒体和金融机构发起了网络攻击。<ref name="hackread" />2016年6月13日，韩国警方表示，朝鲜黑客攻击了160个韩国政府机构和企业逾14万台电脑，植入恶意代码，为大规模网络攻击的长期计划奠定基础。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bbc.com/zhongwen/simp/business/2016/06/160613_north_korea_hacker|title=韩国：朝鲜黑客攻击韩国机构窃取逾4万文件|date=2016-06-13|accessdate=2016-09-05|archive-date=2019-06-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190615034921/https://www.bbc.com/zhongwen/simp/business/2016/06/160613_north_korea_hacker|dead-url=no}}</ref>朝鲜重视网络战，其中一个原因就是网络战更节省成本。<ref name="hackread" />

韩国[[No_Cut_News|No Cut News]]报道称朝鲜政府还通过在[[金策工业综合大学|金策工业综合大学]]和[[金日成综合大学|金日成综合大学]]训练[[黑客|黑客]]来从海外获利。<ref>{{cite news | first = Dae-hui (대희) | last = Lee (이) | script-title = ko:北 '엘리트 해커' 사이버 외화벌이 | date = 2011-08-05 | url = http://www.nocutnews.co.kr/show.asp?idx=1879564 | work = Nocut News | accessdate = 2011-08-21 | language = ko | archive-date = 2012-03-25 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120325084859/http://www.nocutnews.co.kr/show.asp?idx=1879564 | dead-url = no }}</ref>例如，有一组黑客驻扎在中国的[[沈阳|沈阳]]，开发并销售针对《[[天堂_(游戏)|天堂]]》游戏的外挂程序。2011年5月，有一位韩国公民因为购买了该程序而被逮捕。<ref>{{cite news | first = Hye-rim (혜림) | last = Bae (배) | title = 北해커부대, '게임머니'S/W 팔아 외화벌이 | date = 2011-05-06 | url = http://news.mt.co.kr/mtview.php?no=2011050611242179104 | work = Money Today | accessdate = 2011-05-06 | language = ko | archive-date = 2019-06-13 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190613012843/http://news.mt.co.kr/mtview.php?no=2011050611242179104 | dead-url = no }}</ref>

2014年11月发生的[[索尼影业遭黑客攻击事件|索尼影业遭黑客攻击事件]]被[[美国联邦调查局|美国联邦调查局]]认定与朝鲜政府有关。<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/2014/12/19/sony-the-interview-hackers-gop/20635449/ | title = FBI confirms North Korea behind Sony hack | first1 = Elizabeth | last1 = Weise | first2 = Kevin | last2 = Johnson | work = [[USA_Today|USA Today]] | date = December 19, 2014 | accessdate = December 19, 2014 | archive-date = 2020-12-14 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201214150218/https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/2014/12/19/sony-the-interview-hackers-gop/20635449/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>12月19日至21日，朝鲜的互联网访问遇到了技术困难。22日，朝鲜完全失去互联网连接，美国被怀疑是幕后主使。<ref name=NYT2014>[[David_E._Sanger|Sanger, David E.]]; Perlroth, Nicole (December 22, 2014). [http://www.nytimes.com/2014/12/23/world/asia/attack-is-suspected-as-north-korean-internet-collapses.html?_r=0 "North Korea Loses Its Link to the Internet."] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2014/12/23/world/asia/attack-is-suspected-as-north-korean-internet-collapses.html?_r=0 |date=20210302103009 }} ''[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]''. Retrieved December 23, 2014.</ref>23日，经过九个小时的网络中断之后，朝鲜互联网恢复了正常连接，<ref>Ford, Dana (December 23, 2014). [http://www.cnn.com/2014/12/22/world/asia/north-korea-internet/index.html "North Korea's Internet back up after disruption."] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cnn.com/2014/12/22/world/asia/north-korea-internet/index.html |date=20210324193158 }} ''[[CNN|CNN]]''. Retrieved December 23, 2014.</ref>尽管还不太稳定。<ref>[http://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-30584093 "North Korea partially back online after internet collapse."] {{Wayback|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-30584093 |date=20161115154344 }} ''[[BBC|BBC]]''. 23 December 2014. Retrieved 23 December 2014.</ref>22日至24日，朝鲜互联网中断了七次，其中包括23日的两次中断。<ref name=Sydney2014/>27日，朝鲜互联网再度中断。<ref>Slattery, Denis (December 28, 2014). [http://www.nydailynews.com/news/world/north-korea-suffers-nationwide-internet-3g-mobile-blackout-article-1.2058538 "North Korea suffers nationwide Internet, 3G mobile network blackout."] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/world/north-korea-suffers-nationwide-internet-3g-mobile-blackout-article-1.2058538 |date=20210125021604 }} ''[[New_York_Daily_News|New York Daily News]]''. Retrieved December 28, 2014.</ref>对于美国是否为这次网络中断的幕后主使，[[白宫|白宫]]拒绝置评。互联网安全专家表示这次网络中断的原因无法判断。监测全球互联网联网状况的美国公司Dyn Research首席科学家吉姆·考伊认为可能是[[拒绝服务攻击|拒绝服务攻击]]或其他原因。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://m.ftchinese.com/story/001059798|title=朝鲜与互联网联系曾被中断|date=2014-12-23|publisher=FT中文网|accessdate=2016-09-05|archive-date=2019-06-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190611051046/http://m.ftchinese.com/story/001059798|dead-url=no}}</ref>类似的网络中断在2013年3月也发生过，当时持续了一天半。<ref name=Sydney2014>Satter, Raphael; Sullivan, Eileen (December 25, 2014). [http://www.smh.com.au/digital-life/digital-life-news/north-korea-outage-a-case-study-in-online-uncertainties-20141224-12dltr.html "North Korea outage a case study in online uncertainties."] {{Wayback|url=http://www.smh.com.au/digital-life/digital-life-news/north-korea-outage-a-case-study-in-online-uncertainties-20141224-12dltr.html |date=20170925231946 }} ''[[The_Sydney_Morning_Herald|The Sydney Morning Herald]]''. Retrieved December 25, 2014.</ref>

== 商业活动 ==
除了对外宣传网站之外，朝鲜也有若干从事对外商业活动的网站。2002年朝鲜方面曾与一家韩国公司合作开设了面向韩国人的在线[[赌博|赌博]]网站（在韩国，在线赌博属于违法行为），但该网站已经被关闭。<ref name=lankov244>{{cite news |url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/opinon/2009/02/166_13540.html |date=12 December 2007 |title=Surfing Net in North Korea |author=[[Andrei_Lankov|Andrei Lankov]] |work=Korea Times |accessdate=30 May 2016 |archive-date=2016-03-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303174112/http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/opinon/2009/02/166_13540.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>2007年下半年，朝鲜方面与一家匿名的中国公司共同开设了第一家[[网络购物|网络购物]]网站，并命名为“[[千里马_(网站)|千里马]]”，不过该网站也已停止运作。<ref>Kelly Olson, [http://www.wtop.com/?nid=108&pid=0&sid=1338399&page=1 "Elusive Web Site Offers N. Korean Goods"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.wtop.com/?nid=108&pid=0&sid=1338399&page=1 |date=20160304084107 }}, ''WTOPnews.com'', February 4, 2008. Retrieved on April 27, 2008.</ref>2012年8月，[[高丽航空|高丽航空]]开通了网上售票服务，用户可以订购从[[平壤|平壤]]飞往中国[[北京|北京]]和[[沈阳|沈阳]]以及俄罗斯[[符拉迪沃斯托克|符拉迪沃斯托克]]的航班机票，<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bbc.com/zhongwen/simp/world/2012/10/121024_nkorea_airline|title=朝鲜高丽航空开放互联网订票|date=2012-10-24|publisher=BBC中文网|accessdate=2016-09-05|archive-date=2019-06-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190614024209/https://www.bbc.com/zhongwen/simp/world/2012/10/121024_nkorea_airline|dead-url=no}}</ref>该网站至今依然正常运作。

2013年3月5日，[[海盗湾|海盗湾]]声称为了逃避[[版权|版权]]所带来的法律问题，决定在朝鲜设立服务器，但事后海盗湾自己证明相关说法都只是[[恶作剧|恶作剧]]。<ref>{{cite news|title = Pirate Bay North Korea move a hoax|url = http://www.news.com.au/technology/pirate-bay-north-korea-move-a-hoax/story-e6frfro0-1226592461141|newspaper = news.com.au|language = en|accessdate = 2016-09-05|archive-date = 2013-07-02|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20130702021925/http://www.news.com.au/technology/pirate-bay-north-korea-move-a-hoax/story-e6frfro0-1226592461141|dead-url = no}}</ref>

